tips.text: Reviewed in the TODAY newspaper on 4 Jan 2016.
They serve Dried ramen, not the usual soupy ramen ....
Baking needs sold here :)
Great view of the Marina Bay Sands. Nice open view at the upstairs bar.
Yes, their bread samples are back! Hades bread will blow you away.
Free salad bar at dinner time with every main meal! Be quick for the pudding! Runs out fast :(
Not hard to find!
Sashimi rice bowl was yum!
Staff were extremely friendly and helpful ! The spaces are big in size and have all the proper appliances!
Brown rice salad with some chicken and assorted veggies is good here. Really healthy options, but nice big portions also.
Pork ears and the spicy oriental bolognaise are must tries.
Steaks were good. But on the pricey side. And extremely irritating waiters who keep trying to get us to order more.
Neapolitan pizza direct from Italy via Brooklyn NY. Best crust in Singapore. Takes 30 hours to make dough and then pizza cooks in 90 seconds via wood burning oven.
The spicy fragrant flavour is the best, but you need to be able to handle your szechuan peppers
Authentic italian restaurant with an amazing hospitality. Ask Mr. Bui Ban Tu Leo for a "Italian Diplomático" cocktail, a mix of Reserva Exclusiva with iconic italian spirits.
